    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3 due to the single-configuration nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol; this shortfall is accepted given the standardized regulatory context and the strong performance across all quantitative QoI comparisons (maximum E/uval 0.85, maximum relative difference 3.0%). The overall credibility evidence supports the conclusion that the FEA ensemble is sufficiently credible for the stated context of use.",
